@startuml
title SageStore ERP Readiness Gap Map

skinparam packageStyle rectangle
skinparam shadowing false

package "Implemented ERP MVP" {
  [Qt Desktop Client]
  [HTTP Server]
  [SQLite Repositories]
  [Inventory / Purchase / Sales / Management / Logs / Analytics]
}

package "Missing ERP Foundations" {
  [Company Ownership]
  [Storage Scope]
  [Stock Movement Ledger]
  [Documents / Attachments]
  [Import / Export Jobs]
  [Installer / Upgrade Path]
  [Generic Product Attributes Activation]
}

package "Validation and Release" {
  [Qt Unit Tests]
  [Server Unit + Contract Tests]
  [GUI Startup Smoke]
  [Live GUI Fullstack Tests]
}

[Qt Desktop Client] --> [HTTP Server]
[HTTP Server] --> [SQLite Repositories]
[Inventory / Purchase / Sales / Management / Logs / Analytics] --> [Company Ownership]
[Inventory / Purchase / Sales / Management / Logs / Analytics] --> [Storage Scope]
[Inventory / Purchase / Sales / Management / Logs / Analytics] --> [Stock Movement Ledger]
[Inventory / Purchase / Sales / Management / Logs / Analytics] --> [Documents / Attachments]
[Inventory / Purchase / Sales / Management / Logs / Analytics] --> [Import / Export Jobs]
[HTTP Server] --> [Installer / Upgrade Path]
[Inventory / Purchase / Sales / Management / Logs / Analytics] --> [Generic Product Attributes Activation]

[Qt Unit Tests] --> [Qt Desktop Client]
[Server Unit + Contract Tests] --> [HTTP Server]
[GUI Startup Smoke] --> [Qt Desktop Client]
[Live GUI Fullstack Tests] --> [Qt Desktop Client]
[Live GUI Fullstack Tests] --> [HTTP Server]

note right of [Live GUI Fullstack Tests]
This turn adds live GUI workflow coverage
without introducing a second UI automation stack.
end note
@enduml
